<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n08157c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08157c">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08157c"> 157(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Iona = Jonah </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: St Columba&apos;s biographer, Adomna&aacute;n, equates the saint&apos;s name with the Hebrew Jona, as both words mean &lsquo;dove&rsquo;. This influenced some commentators, beginning with T. Pennant, who, in his <cite>A Tour in Scotland and Voyage to the Hebrides</cite> (1774), applies the same principle to Iona. See Adomna&aacute;n of Iona, <cite>Life of St Columba</cite> (London: Penguin Books, 1995), 104, 258-9. <font color="green">[Vincent Deane.]</font>  <br>Raphael transcription: <a name="c03018l" href="c03all.htm#c03018l">VI.C.03:018(l)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
